1
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.580
Don't tell me you're back to spying on Adrian.

2
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:18.580
You two are together now.

3
00:00:18.580 --> 00:00:22.040
I'm not spying on him, I'm spying on the girl he's running with.

4
00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:23.040
Sublime?

5
00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:24.520
Yeah, I want to know more about her.

6
00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:26.120
Why don't you just ask Adrian?

7
00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:27.120
Already did.

8
00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:28.120
And?

9
00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:29.120
And nothing.

10
00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:30.640
What do you mean, nothing?

11
00:00:30.640 --> 00:00:33.920
I said, surely you two tell things to each other when you're running together every

12
00:00:33.920 --> 00:00:34.920
morning.

13
00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:35.920
You're practically holding hands.

14
00:00:35.920 --> 00:00:36.920
And what did he say?

15
00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:37.920
Nothing.

16
00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:39.840
They run, but they don't say anything to each other.

17
00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:40.840
Not a word.

18
00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:42.720
But it's impossible to be silent next to someone for that long.

19
00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:43.720
They must be hiding something.

20
00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:44.720
There, there!

21
00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:45.720
Oh!

22
00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:46.720
She said something!

23
00:00:46.720 --> 00:00:47.720
Oh, wait!

24
00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:48.720
Oh, no.

25
00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:49.720
No, no, no.

26
00:00:49.720 --> 00:00:50.720
She just sneezed.

27
00:00:50.720 --> 00:00:51.720
Could it be that you're a little jealous?

28
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:52.720
Me?

29
00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:53.720
Jealous?

30
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:54.720
Ha!

31
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:55.720
No way.

32
00:00:55.720 --> 00:00:56.720
See?

33
00:00:56.720 --> 00:00:57.720
Since Sublime is now friends with Adrian, I should become friends with Sublime.

34
00:00:57.720 --> 00:00:58.720
Are you following?

35
00:00:58.720 --> 00:00:59.720
It just makes sense!

36
00:00:59.720 --> 00:01:04.000
The friends of my boyfriend, who aren't yet my friends, are my future friends.

37
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:07.080
Meaning, I can't get this wrong, except the target isn't just anyone.

38
00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:10.360
Sublime Barlet was born in Belgium, according to the website of the city Mucron, where she

39
00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:11.360
grew up.

40
00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:14.040
She was, and I quote, "the pride of the city."

41
00:01:14.040 --> 00:01:15.160
And for good reasons.

42
00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:17.080
She won the first prize at the conservatoire.

43
00:01:17.080 --> 00:01:18.400
She plays the harp and the flute.

44
00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:19.400
She speaks five languages.

45
00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:21.600
Her parents settled in Paris after their divorce.

46
00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:25.120
And even though she hasn't been in Paris for long, Sublime has already joined several

47
00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:26.860
associations and clubs.

48
00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:31.240
She also won gold in the para-athletics 100 and 400 meter, and is currently training for

49
00:01:31.240 --> 00:01:35.640
the upcoming world championship by running every day, every morning with Adrian, supposedly

50
00:01:35.640 --> 00:01:36.640
without speaking.

51
00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:41.640
I'll never measure up to a girl like that, Alia!

52
00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:43.640
I'll never be as Sublime as she is!

53
00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:46.200
You're putting too much pressure on yourself, girl.

54
00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:48.640
If you want to get to know her, just go talk to her.

55
00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:49.640
Too risky.

56
00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:51.520
You have one chance to make a good first impression.

57
00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:54.000
Okay, so what are you going to do?

58
00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:58.560
I'm going to show her that I can measure up, because that's what it means to be a friend.

59
00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:04.200
It's showing that you're here, always, and that you're resourceful in any and all situations.

60
00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:10.400
Okay, well, my dear resourceful friend, I'll leave you to your mess-making, and we'll catch

61
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:11.400
up later.

62
00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:17.640
Hey, wait, Alia, aren't you going to stop her from making a mess of things?

63
00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:18.640
You know Marinette.

64
00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:21.320
Once she's made up her mind, it's hard to convince her that she's wrong.

65
00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.320
Besides, mistakes are just learning opportunities.

66
00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:25.760
And Marinette loves to learn.

67
00:02:25.760 --> 00:02:30.080
Still, keep an eye on it, Tiki.

68
00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:35.400
In the daytime, I'm Marinette, just a normal girl, with a normal life.

69
00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:40.800
But there's something about me that no one knows yet, because I've got a secret.

70
00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:46.800
Miraculous, simply the best, after the death when things go wrong.

71
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:52.800
Miraculous, the lucky ends, the powers are always so strong.

72
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:56.440
Miraculous, Miraculous.

73
00:02:56.440 --> 00:03:20.640
Marinette, are you sure this is the best way to become friends with Sublime?

74
00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:30.040
Of course, Tiki, everyone loves having a friend unexpectedly show up to help.

75
00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:36.040
Now's my chance!

76
00:03:36.040 --> 00:03:53.640
You ate it all up, my little baby birds.

77
00:03:53.640 --> 00:03:54.640
This is a chance I can't miss.

78
00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:55.640
I know where to get chopsticks.

79
00:03:55.640 --> 00:04:13.320
Friends, I know how stressful city life can be.

80
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:17.880
Which is why I'll play a little harp piece for you all.

81
00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.400
I just need a little luck.

82
00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:25.240
Like, if one of her harp strings could break, then I'd find a replacement for it.

83
00:04:25.240 --> 00:04:35.240
It would be so moved, it would signal the beginning of our friendship and-

84
00:04:35.240 --> 00:05:03.240
I'm sorry, major string emergency.

85
00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:05.220
I'll be waiting for you by the entrance.

86
00:05:05.220 --> 00:05:07.120
I'm so proud of you, sweetie.

87
00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:09.720
Okay, dad, I'll see you soon.

88
00:05:09.720 --> 00:05:11.400
The trial is starting earlier.

89
00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:13.640
Would you mind picking up my homework assignments for me?

90
00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:14.640
Not at all.

91
00:05:14.640 --> 00:05:15.640
Don't turn around.

92
00:05:15.640 --> 00:05:20.840
There's a girl with ponytails behind you, hiding behind a plant.

93
00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:22.760
Could she be your girlfriend by any chance?

94
00:05:22.760 --> 00:05:24.840
Yeah, that description sounds fitting.

95
00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:28.240
He's talking to her, she's talking to him, which means they're talking!

96
00:05:28.240 --> 00:05:30.480
Could Adrian have lied to me?

97
00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:32.480
Maybe it's because they're in the same class!

98
00:05:32.480 --> 00:05:33.480
Ancient Greek class!

99
00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:34.480
Oh no!

100
00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:37.400
They're gonna speak in code so that no one can understand them!

101
00:05:37.400 --> 00:05:40.680
Do you know why your girlfriend has been following me around all morning?

102
00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:42.440
Oh, don't worry about that.

103
00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:46.680
I think she just wants to be friends and get to know you, but it's not always that easy

104
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:47.680
for her.

105
00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:49.440
How unique!

106
00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:50.440
That's Marinette for you.

107
00:05:50.440 --> 00:05:53.520
How about arranging something for the three of us to meet?

108
00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:54.520
That's a great idea.

109
00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.520
I'll go ask her.

110
00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:56.520
Great.

111
00:05:56.520 --> 00:05:57.520
I have to go.

112
00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:58.520
See you tomorrow.

113
00:05:58.520 --> 00:05:59.520
Good luck with the trial.

114
00:05:59.520 --> 00:06:00.520
Thank you!

115
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:01.520
I've been caught!

116
00:06:01.520 --> 00:06:05.520
Oh no!

117
00:06:05.520 --> 00:06:09.520
She's only following her!

118
00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:13.840
Now she's furious and decided to stop being friends with Adrian and to leave the school!

119
00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:15.920
Are you really sure about any of this, Marinette?

120
00:06:15.920 --> 00:06:16.920
Yes.

121
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:18.800
But I'm going to fix my mistake!

122
00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:22.080
Because if Sublime is no longer friends with Adrian because of me, then Adrian won't love

123
00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:23.080
me anymore!

124
00:06:23.080 --> 00:06:32.800
This will be the end of our relationship and the end of everything!

125
00:06:32.800 --> 00:06:33.800
Sublime!

126
00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:34.800
Forgive me!

127
00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:52.040
I've been the worst friend ever!

128
00:06:52.040 --> 00:06:53.920
Adrian let her manage on her own!

129
00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:54.920
What?

130
00:06:54.920 --> 00:06:56.600
I'm just giving her a little help, that's all.

131
00:06:56.600 --> 00:07:00.800
If you really want what's good for her, then stop helping her every time she's faced with

132
00:07:00.800 --> 00:07:01.800
a challenge.

133
00:07:01.800 --> 00:07:03.720
Or she'll never learn to get by on her own.

134
00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:31.440
She's been in there for at least twenty minutes, hasn't she?

135
00:07:31.440 --> 00:07:32.440
Maybe she's encountered a problem?

136
00:07:32.440 --> 00:07:33.440
Yes, yes!

137
00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:35.160
She probably needs help from a friend!

138
00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:36.160
I'm going in!

139
00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:37.160
Wait, Marinette!

140
00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:38.160
What is it?

141
00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:39.160
We don't even know why we're here!

142
00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:40.920
I was right from the beginning.

143
00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:41.920
I'll talk to her.

144
00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:42.920
Hi, Tiki!

145
00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:50.040
Where did she go?

146
00:07:50.040 --> 00:07:54.180
If you agree to sponsor my daughter, you won't be disappointed, Mr. Roth.

147
00:07:54.180 --> 00:07:56.160
What's your daughter's marketing strength?

148
00:07:56.160 --> 00:07:57.160
She's the fastest runner.

149
00:07:57.160 --> 00:08:01.040
Look, Sublime won gold in one hundred and four hundred meter at the Regional Parathletics.

150
00:08:01.040 --> 00:08:02.040
Gold?

151
00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:03.040
Yeah, right.

152
00:08:03.040 --> 00:08:04.040
More like junk.

153
00:08:04.040 --> 00:08:05.040
It's symbolic!

154
00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:06.040
Symbolic?

155
00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:07.040
Ha!

156
00:08:07.040 --> 00:08:08.560
Symbolic money is worth nothing.

157
00:08:08.560 --> 00:08:12.840
I told you, Caroline, finding a sponsor isn't easy, but it's okay.

158
00:08:12.840 --> 00:08:13.840
Sublime has time.

159
00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:14.840
She's young.

160
00:08:14.840 --> 00:08:15.840
Mr. Roth, wait!

161
00:08:15.840 --> 00:08:20.640
At the World Championship, it'll be a real gold medal, one hundred percent pure gold!

162
00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:21.640
Ah!

163
00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:23.320
This changes everything!

164
00:08:23.320 --> 00:08:27.320
In that case, if I do sponsor her and she wins, I keep the medal.

165
00:08:27.320 --> 00:08:28.840
Consider this an advance payment.

166
00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:30.480
I don't like the way he operates.

167
00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:34.400
Without a sponsor, Sublime won't be allowed to enter the World Championship.

168
00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:36.120
Is that what you want for your daughter?

169
00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:39.920
For her to fail again and again like her father?

170
00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:41.600
We accept your offer, Mr. Roth.

171
00:08:41.600 --> 00:08:42.600
Easy, easy.

172
00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:44.320
I'm not offering anything yet.

173
00:08:44.320 --> 00:08:47.760
I want to see what your daughter's worth on the track first.

174
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:48.760
Ha!

175
00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:56.280
Anaconda has villain disintegrated Sublime, leaving only her prostheses behind!

176
00:08:56.280 --> 00:08:57.280
Tiki!

177
00:08:57.280 --> 00:08:59.960
Marinette, maybe there's a more logical explanation.

178
00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:00.960
Marinette!

179
00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:05.720
Surely you're not going to disturb her right now?

180
00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:06.720
You're right.

181
00:09:06.720 --> 00:09:07.720
Yes.

182
00:09:07.720 --> 00:09:08.720
I'll wait.

183
00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:09.720
Huh?

184
00:09:09.720 --> 00:09:31.040
I know you're in here.

185
00:09:31.040 --> 00:09:35.360
I know you're hiding, lurking in the shadows, ready to leap out and stop me from winning.

186
00:09:35.360 --> 00:09:37.280
But I won't let you!

187
00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:40.880
When you come, I will be ready, and I will overcome you.

188
00:09:40.880 --> 00:09:56.400
No one can stop me from getting what I want, especially not you!

189
00:09:56.400 --> 00:09:59.400
She hates me because she can't have what she wants.

190
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.400
What does it mean?

191
00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:05.280
She's in love with Adrian!

192
00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:08.780
My water bottle!

193
00:10:08.780 --> 00:10:13.160
She's coming back to overcome me!

194
00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:20.360
I'm Soapinator, and not at all, Marinette Dupain-Chang!

195
00:10:20.360 --> 00:10:28.120
I hate dirt and clean everything in my path!

196
00:10:28.120 --> 00:10:33.920
Listen Marinette, or Soapinator, I'll happily have a chat with you after my trial, okay?

197
00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:36.040
I really don't have time now.

198
00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:37.520
So wait for me here.

199
00:10:37.520 --> 00:10:44.040
Do not move, and do not follow me.

200
00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:45.200
I no longer have a choice.

201
00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:46.200
Tiki!

202
00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:47.200
Wait, what are you going to do?

203
00:10:47.200 --> 00:10:52.320
I can feel that she didn't fall for my costume, but if I become Ladybug, she'll be convinced

204
00:10:52.320 --> 00:10:54.320
that I was akumatized for real!

205
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:55.320
Marinette, this is a-

206
00:10:55.320 --> 00:11:08.680
Hold tight sweetheart, I have to do a final adjustment on your right prosthesis.

207
00:11:08.680 --> 00:11:12.760
If you find it too difficult you have the right to give up.

208
00:11:12.760 --> 00:11:14.480
You know I'll always love you.

209
00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:18.920
It's okay to be afraid, and it's okay not to succeed all the time.

210
00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:19.920
Thanks, Dad.

211
00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:22.080
Don't listen to your loser of a father.

212
00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:26.560
I know it's in here, fear is always ready to leap out and stop you from winning, but

213
00:11:26.560 --> 00:11:27.560
you're ready.

214
00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:31.920
You just need to overcome that fear and turn it into a strength that will make you soar.

215
00:11:31.920 --> 00:11:35.080
Remember, no one can stop you from getting what you want.

216
00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:42.720
You're my champion, you're sublime.

217
00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:53.240
On your mark, get set, go!

218
00:11:53.240 --> 00:12:03.760
Where is the akumatized villain?

219
00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:06.400
Where is Sofina?

220
00:12:06.400 --> 00:12:09.120
Don't go Mr. Roth!

221
00:12:09.120 --> 00:12:10.120
Everything's okay, Ladybug.

222
00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:12.800
It's just Marinette Dupain-Cheng.

223
00:12:12.800 --> 00:12:13.800
Marinette Dupain-Cheng?

224
00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:16.560
Yeah, she's a girl from my school.

225
00:12:16.560 --> 00:12:22.320
She pretended to be akumatized and disguised herself as soap, bucket eater, or something.

226
00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:27.120
My friend Adrienne explained that whenever she likes someone, she starts to act peculiar,

227
00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.040
which means she likes me I guess.

228
00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:32.480
So there's no danger, I'm not hurt.

229
00:12:32.480 --> 00:12:35.360
Everything is... fine.

230
00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:38.640
This is a disaster, we've just lost months of work.

231
00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:44.080
We've done it once, we'll do it again, Dad.

232
00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:46.680
Give her another chance, this is just a setback!

233
00:12:46.680 --> 00:12:57.360
Precisely, time is money, and a setback is not money in my wallet!

234
00:12:57.360 --> 00:12:58.560
Hello ma'am.

235
00:12:58.560 --> 00:13:03.240
Forgive my intrusion, but I seem to sense a considerable frustration.

236
00:13:03.240 --> 00:13:04.920
People are letting you down, aren't they?

237
00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:06.720
They're not up to your expectations.

238
00:13:06.720 --> 00:13:09.200
I can't be as sublime as my daughter.

239
00:13:09.200 --> 00:13:10.200
You're right.

240
00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:15.160
The world would be sublime if people could be better versions of themselves.

241
00:13:15.160 --> 00:13:16.160
Like your daughter?

242
00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:19.720
I'd give you the power to make everything better, you know.

243
00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:21.320
Only if you agree, of course.

244
00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:24.000
That'd be the best thing that could happen to me.

245
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:26.160
And what should I call you?

246
00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:27.160
Sublimation!

247
00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:36.000
I know why you're hiding, but I'm going to help you surpass your fear so you can carry

248
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.320
on with your mission.

249
00:13:37.320 --> 00:13:38.320
Be better!

250
00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:39.320
Yeah, let's resume the race.

251
00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:40.320
Let's go on to the trial.

252
00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:41.320
Well, now someone actually has been akumatized.

253
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:42.320
Don't worry, I'll protect you.

254
00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:43.320
How dare you pretend you're protecting my daughter when you've destroyed her trial!

255
00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:44.320
Kabaline!

256
00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:45.320
Think you could look at me, sweetheart?

257
00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:46.320
Thanks to sublimation, Ladybug is finally about to become a better superhero!

258
00:13:46.320 --> 00:13:47.320
I'm sincerely sorry.

259
00:13:47.320 --> 00:13:48.320
I'm sorry.

260
00:13:48.320 --> 00:14:10.680
It was unfortunate misunderstanding, but please reject the akuma, and I promise I'll

261
